7.1 Three Stress Conditions and Failure Predictions
Section 4.4.4 established that LLM hallucination is not superimposition collapse. For a UOO-trained system, however, a precise failure mode prediction exists:
Prediction: A UOO system that successfully maintains non-separable representations will, under the following stress conditions, see its representations degrade from Regime II to Regime III:
-
